"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-sports-team-usa-kaillie-humphries-rips-newsom-response-alleged-california-fraud-raises-olympic-concerns\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92026 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byLSEG.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.428281773444357e-40, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. Olympic bobsledding star Kaillie Humphries reveals her support of President Trump, including his protection of women's sports, his celebration of the men's hockey team, and immigration enforcement as a legal immigrant herself from Canada.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 365, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaillie Humphries\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\"}, {\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999931417090543, \"rank\": 6.858329924977054e-06, \"text\": \"President Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999998818079873, \"rank\": 1.1818743923084184e-07, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic bobsled legend Kaillie Humphries is a tax-paying Californian, and she is not happy about the response by Gov.Gavin Newsomto recent allegations of fraud in the state, especially with the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics on the horizon.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaillie Humphries\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Newsom came under fire Tuesday night after his press office posted a response to independent journalist Nick Shirley'sinvestigation of alleged fraudin California.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 921, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9091479605995476, \"rank\": 0.09993093937808013, \"text\": \"Nick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999979277339306, \"rank\": 2.071500790252787e-06, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The post included an AI image depicting Shirley covered in cameras with a speech bubble that said, \\\"Hey, can I see your kids?\\\"\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999999499778, \"rank\": 4.865958308291075e-11, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CLICK HERE FOR MORE SPORTS COVERAGE ON FOXNEWS.COM  Humphries told Fox News Digital her reaction, raising concerns over the impact it could have on the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics.\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As aCalifornia resident, I am deeply concerned about the reports of alleged financial fraud and Governor Newsom's apathy to it.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from the reality that any financial fraud is wrong, the fact that this allegedly happened in the state that is slated to host the 2028 Olympics is even more concerning.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are a multi-billion dollar event that requires substantial governmental support to ensure it runs correctly,\\\" Humphries said.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Olympic host cities around the world have struggled with financial fraud surrounding hosting the Olympics for years.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"America is not immune from these problems, as the Salt Lake City Olympics in 2002 was tainted with a bribery scandal.\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1901, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2002_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999927336023921, \"rank\": 7.266925652165714e-05, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2002_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2002_Winter_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ahead of America hosting the world in the LA 28 Olympics, California and its leadership, including Governor Newsom, need to address these serious allegations and ensure that all U.S. taxpayer money spent at the Olympics is properly accounted for.\\\"\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999979277339306, \"rank\": 2.071500790252787e-06, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9899640315911385, \"rank\": 0.010137709458890526, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Newsom's office has provided a statement upon Fox News Digital's request for a response to Humphries.\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our office does not typically respond to commentary from individuals who are not directly involved in or informed about the matter at hand,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Under Governor Newsom's leadership, California is leading the nation in PREVENTING fraud, waste, and abuse - protecting billions of dollars intended for families, students, seniors, and communities,\\\" a spokesperson said, adding a link to a state website supposedly dedicated to stopping fraud.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999979277339306, \"rank\": 2.071500790252787e-06, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"OLYMPIC LEGEND KAILLIE HUMPHRIES SPEAKS OUT AGAINST SJSU FOR VOLLEYBALL SCANDAL HANDLING, BACKS BROOKE SLUSSER  Humphries moved to San Diego, immigrating legally from Canada in a process that spanned the late 2010s to early 2020s.\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 3011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KAILLIE HUMPHRIES\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\"}, {\"begin\": 2916, \"end\": 2921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"score\": 0.9810885500401344, \"rank\": 0.019275986820116518, \"text\": \"Diego\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\"}, {\"begin\": 2948, \"end\": 2954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999998818079873, \"rank\": 1.1818743923084184e-07, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She famously transitioned from Team Canada to Team USA, becoming the only women's bobsledder to win gold medals for both teams, all while enduring an intense legal immigration process.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3043, \"end\": 3054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.996608884655535, \"rank\": 0.003396486795405621, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3058, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999564352, \"rank\": 4.358250094684087e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, she is a new mom in San Diego with her husband Travis, navigating the state's challenges.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3227, \"end\": 3232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"score\": 0.9810885500401344, \"rank\": 0.019275986820116518, \"text\": \"Diego\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\"}, {\"begin\": 3250, \"end\": 3256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"score\": 0.9999999514520835, \"rank\": 4.8541507508429155e-08, \"text\": \"Travis\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Manawa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Humphries revealed she is a Republican and proud supporter of PresidentDonald Trumpin an interview with Fox News Digital shortly after she won bronze at the Milan Cortina Winter Olympics.\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\", \"score\": 0.9999973426992091, \"rank\": 2.6567017529324544e-06, \"text\": \"Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Republican_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 3398, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}, {\"begin\": 3451, \"end\": 3456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.9999765739778003, \"rank\": 2.3423920367789352e-05, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.991105022718361e-17, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She spoke out in support of Trump's goals of protecting women's sports, immigration law enforcement, making IVF more accessible, and she even defended the U.S. men's hockey team for their association with Trump after backlash from the left.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3510, \"end\": 3515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999916705802587, \"rank\": 8.329487004749898e-06, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 3637, \"end\": 3641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9899640315911385, \"rank\": 0.010137709458890526, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3687, \"end\": 3692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999916705802587, \"rank\": 8.329487004749898e-06, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Humphries then became the first U.S. Olympian to give the Order of Ikkos medal to a president when she gave it to Trump at a women's history month event at the White House last week.\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1789379793191305e-13, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said she received backlash after revealing herTrump supportin her initial interview with Fox News Digital.\", \"from\": 3908, \"to\": 4018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4001, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have had some people not agree with my opinions and make it very known,\\\" Humphries previously said.\", \"from\": 4020, \"to\": 4122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CLICK HERE TO DOWNLOAD THE FOX NEWS APP  Kaillie Humphries, U.S. Olympic bronze medalist bobsled athlete, presents the Order of Ikkos to U.S. President Donald Trump during a Women's History Month event in the East Room of the White House in Washington, D.C., U.S., on Thursday, March 12, 2026.\", \"from\": 4124, \"to\": 4417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4147, \"end\": 4154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Fox_and_the_Cat\", \"score\": 0.9999999977148946, \"rank\": 2.284911855518603e-09, \"text\": \"THE FOX\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Fox_and_the_Cat\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Fox_and_the_Cat\"}, {\"begin\": 4151, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX NEWS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}, {\"begin\": 4165, \"end\": 4182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaillie Humphries\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaillie_Humphries\"}, {\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999998804387431, \"rank\": 1.194243430847927e-07, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 4350, \"end\": 4361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999410238999418, \"rank\": 4.836726774173988e-05, \"text\": \"White House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9999671379184323, \"rank\": 3.2863154305906696e-05, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.8239187589904841, \"rank\": 0.21371184542149976, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}, {\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9999671379184323, \"rank\": 3.2863154305906696e-05, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every year, March is designated Women's History Month by presidential proclamation.\", \"from\": 4418, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Al Drago/Bloomberg)  \\\"A lot of name-calling.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4505, \"end\": 4510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivan_Drago\", \"score\": 0.9999996647293863, \"rank\": 3.35188517973177e-07, \"text\": \"Drago\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivan_Drago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivan_Drago\"}, {\"begin\": 4511, \"end\": 4520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999890101209, \"rank\": 1.0984488670341222e-08, \"text\": \"Bloomberg\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You get called every name and word under the sun humanly possible \\u2026 and, at the end of the day, politics can be very emotional for people, and I understand that.\", \"from\": 4547, \"to\": 4708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And everyone is entitled to their own beliefs and what they represent.\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's their opinion, and I do not have to like it or agree with it.\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish it was different, but that's how it works.\\\"\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Fox News Digital'ssports coverage on X, and subscribe tothe Fox News Sports Huddle newsletter.\", \"from\": 4903, \"to\": 5004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4910, \"end\": 4918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}, {\"begin\": 4970, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jackson Thompson is a sports reporter for Fox News Digital covering critical political and cultural issues in sports, with an investigative lens.\", \"from\": 5006, \"to\": 5151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5006, \"end\": 5022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999706668927831, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jackson Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jackson_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 5048, \"end\": 5056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.921085983183086e-25, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jackson's reporting has been cited in federal government actions related to the enforcement of Title IX, and in legacy media outlets including The New York Times, The Los Angeles Times, The Philadelphia Inquirer, The Associated Press and ESPN.com.\", \"from\": 5152, \"to\": 5399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5152, \"end\": 5159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.219536305302472e-16, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 5247, \"end\": 5255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0760040685290362e-30, \"text\": \"Title IX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Title_IX\"}, 